2563fe9a019babbcdb8db0725b51adf5ed8326e9.text_content:
Welcome to andOTP! This wizard will guide you through the initial setup process. Please pay attention and read carefully in order to avoid losing data. 

Don't worry, you can still change any of these options later on in the Settings.

f3905a455a69724d5b35b359ae32aa218a9995e2.text_content: To ensure the security of your accounts, andOTP uses encryption to store account data. Here you can choose which method of encryption will be used.

This method will encrypt your data with a key generated from a password or PIN. The main advantage of using this method is that external backup solutions (like Titanium) will work as expected, and it is much less failure-prone than the KeyStore. However, you will have to enter your credentials every time you start andOTP.

501e2e5c249dc28abf8e52d4912f52dd03d21b39.text_content: Here you can setup an authentication method to lock andOTP. Since you have chosen Password / PIN as your encryption method, a password or a PIN must be set to proceed.

8adf75fcdb77501f5fdf32071eb62d88ab762608.text_content: Your settings have been saved, you are now all set to use andOTP!

f0e3fcf04484a44c2dbf19556abddfa5cdcb64a9.text_content: Please confirm authentication to generate your encryption key!

01e88bc3883368add533da8fcfe5459cd578e8c6.text_content: Decide what happens when a Panic Trigger is received
Require authentication after the devices screen has been turned off
Re-lock when going into the background
Require authentication after the app was sent to the background (e.g. by pressing the home button)
Require authentication after the device has been inactive

a8af282e7aeffc6e34854954e7982eb3365fe83f.text_content: The password needs to be at least 6 characters long!
